<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 30 at 1:36PM CST  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Clarke
and southwestern Wilcox Counties through 215 PM CST...
At 135 PM CST, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm 8 miles west of Thomasville, moving east at 35
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Thomasville, Pine Hill and Yellow Bluff.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CST for
south central and southwestern Alabama.</instruction>
